// C3: Physical Sensing Components
instance GreenhouseEnvironmentSensor : DTDFVocab:SensingComponent [
    base:desc "Embedded sensors in GreenhouseDT virtual machine providing prerecorded environmental data for simulation and validation"
    DTDFVocab:producedData GreenhouseEnvironmentDataTransmitted
]

instance AirQualitySensorSet : DTDFVocab:SensingComponent [
    base:desc "Raspberry Pi-equipped sensors for real-time indoor air quality monitoring (CO2, particulate matter, humidity, temperature)"
    DTDFVocab:producedData AirQualityDataTransmitted
]

instance CraneStateSensor : DTDFVocab:SensingComponent [
    base:desc "Physical crane interface collecting state measurements (position, velocity, acceleration, controller feedback, load weight)"
    DTDFVocab:producedData CraneStateDataTransmitted
]

// C4: Physical-to-Virtual Interaction
instance GreenhouseEnvironmentDataTransmitted : DTDFVocab:DataTransmitted [
    DTDFVocab:producedFrom GreenhouseEnvironmentSensor
]

instance AirQualityDataTransmitted : DTDFVocab:DataTransmitted [
    DTDFVocab:producedFrom AirQualitySensorSet
]

instance CraneStateDataTransmitted : DTDFVocab:DataTransmitted [
    DTDFVocab:producedFrom CraneStateSensor
]

// C10: Models/Data
instance GreenhouseBehavioralModel : DTDFVocab:Model [
    base:desc "Behavioral adaptation model for greenhouse climate control using prerecorded data in virtual machine images"
    DTDFVocab:inputTo GreenhouseSimulationEnabler
]

instance AirQualitySimulationModel : DTDFVocab:Model [
    base:desc "AutomationML-based digital twin model for indoor air quality simulation, prediction, and runtime visualization"
    DTDFVocab:inputTo AirQualitySimulationEnabler
]

instance CraneKinematicModel : DTDFVocab:Model [
    base:desc "Mathematical representation of crane movement mechanics enabling trajectory simulation and control"
    DTDFVocab:inputTo CraneControlEnabler
]

instance GreenhouseTimeSeriesData : DTDFVocab:Data [
    base:desc "Structured time-series data stored in InfluxDB for greenhouse environmental parameters"
    DTDFVocab:fromData GreenhouseEnvironmentDataTransmitted
    DTDFVocab:inputTo GreenhouseDataStorageEnabler
]

instance AirQualityTimeSeriesData : DTDFVocab:Data [
    base:desc "Real-time air quality sensor data collected via Raspberry Pi for simulation and prediction"
    DTDFVocab:fromData AirQualityDataTransmitted
    DTDFVocab:inputTo AirQualityDataStorageEnabler
]

instance CraneOperationalData : DTDFVocab:Data [
    base:desc "High-frequency crane state measurements stored in TimescaleDB for trajectory validation"
    DTDFVocab:fromData CraneStateDataTransmitted
    DTDFVocab:inputTo CraneDataStorageEnabler
]

// C11: Enablers
instance GreenhouseSimulationEnabler : DTDFVocab:Enabler [
    base:desc "Virtual machine environment with prerecorded data enabling greenhouse behavioral simulation"
    DTDFVocab:enables GreenhouseControlService, GreenhouseValidationService
]

instance AirQualitySimulationEnabler : DTDFVocab:Enabler [
    base:desc "AutomationML-based runtime environment for air quality simulation and prediction"
    DTDFVocab:enables AirQualityVisualizationService, AirQualityPredictionService
]

instance CraneControlEnabler : DTDFVocab:Enabler [
    base:desc "Kinematic model implementation enabling real-time crane trajectory planning and optimization"
    DTDFVocab:enables CraneOptimalControlService, CraneValidationService
]

instance GreenhouseDataStorageEnabler : DTDFVocab:Enabler [
    base:desc "InfluxDB time-series database for structured greenhouse environmental data storage"
    DTDFVocab:enables GreenhouseHistoricalLoggingService
]

instance AirQualityDataStorageEnabler : DTDFVocab:Enabler [
    base:desc "Raspberry Pi data collection system with AutomationML-compatible sensor formats"
    DTDFVocab:enables AirQualityHistoricalLoggingService
]

instance CraneDataStorageEnabler : DTDFVocab:Enabler [
    base:desc "TimescaleDB database for high-frequency crane operational data storage"
    DTDFVocab:enables CraneHistoricalLoggingService
]

instance MessageBrokerEnabler : DTDFVocab:Enabler [
    base:desc "ActiveMQ message broker facilitating event-driven communication between digital twin components"
    DTDFVocab:enables GreenhouseControlService, AirQualityVisualizationService, CraneValidationService
]

instance AzureCloudEnabler : DTDFVocab:Enabler [
    base:desc "Microsoft Azure tools enabling scalable cloud-based execution for digital twin services"
    DTDFVocab:enables AirQualityPredictionService, AirQualityVisualizationService
]

// C6: Services
instance GreenhouseControlService : DTDFVocab:Service [
    base:desc "Provides real-time adjustment algorithms for greenhouse climate control parameters"
    DTDFVocab:provides GreenhouseClimateOptimizationInsight
]

instance GreenhouseValidationService : DTDFVocab:Service [
    base:desc "Continuously validates greenhouse digital twin accuracy through physical-digital state comparison"
    DTDFVocab:provides GreenhouseSynchronizationInsight
]

instance GreenhouseHistoricalLoggingService : DTDFVocab:Service [
    base:desc "Collects and stores long-term greenhouse operational data for analysis"
    DTDFVocab:provides GreenhouseTrendAnalysisInsight
]

instance AirQualityVisualizationService : DTDFVocab:Service [
    base:desc "Provides runtime visualization dashboards for indoor air quality metrics"
    DTDFVocab:provides AirQualityRuntimeVisualizationInsight
]

instance AirQualityPredictionService : DTDFVocab:Service [
    base:desc "Predicts virus spread risks and air quality dynamics under varying conditions"
    DTDFVocab:provides AirQualityPredictionInsight
]

instance AirQualityHistoricalLoggingService : DTDFVocab:Service [
    base:desc "Stores operational air quality data for trend analysis and validation"
    DTDFVocab:provides AirQualityHistoricalAnalysisInsight
]

instance CraneOptimalControlService : DTDFVocab:Service [
    base:desc "Optimizes crane control parameters for trajectory planning and energy efficiency"
    DTDFVocab:provides CraneTrajectoryOptimizationInsight
]

instance CraneValidationService : DTDFVocab:Service [
    base:desc "Validates digital twin accuracy by comparing simulated and executed crane trajectories"
    DTDFVocab:provides CraneTrajectoryValidationInsight
]

instance CraneHistoricalLoggingService : DTDFVocab:Service [
    base:desc "Logs crane operational data for performance analysis and fault detection"
    DTDFVocab:provides CraneOperationalAnalysisInsight
]

// C17: Insights/Actions
instance GreenhouseClimateOptimizationInsight : DTDFVocab:Insight [
    base:desc "Real-time climate control parameter adjustments for greenhouse environmental optimization"
]

instance GreenhouseSynchronizationInsight : DTDFVocab:Insight [
    base:desc "Real-time synchronization status between physical greenhouse and digital twin"
]

instance GreenhouseTrendAnalysisInsight : DTDFVocab:Insight [
    base:desc "Long-term environmental parameter trends for greenhouse management"
]

instance AirQualityRuntimeVisualizationInsight : DTDFVocab:Insight [
    base:desc "Real-time visualization of indoor air quality metrics from Raspberry Pi sensors"
]

instance AirQualityPredictionInsight : DTDFVocab:Insight [
    base:desc "Predicted virus spread risks and air quality dynamics under simulated conditions"
]

instance AirQualityHistoricalAnalysisInsight : DTDFVocab:Insight [
    base:desc "Historical air quality trends and pattern analysis for system optimization"
]

instance CraneTrajectoryOptimizationInsight : DTDFVocab:Insight [
    base:desc "Optimized crane movement trajectories for energy efficiency and load balancing"
]

instance CraneTrajectoryValidationInsight : DTDFVocab:Insight [
    base:desc "Distance metrics comparing executed and simulated crane trajectories with fault detection"
]

instance CraneOperationalAnalysisInsight : DTDFVocab:Insight [
    base:desc "Operational performance metrics and fault detection alerts for crane maintenance"
]

// C2: Acting Components (from Physical Acting Components - Not in Document, skipped)

instance virtual_to_physical_interaction : DTDFVocab:VirtualToPhysical [
    base:desc "The **Virtual-to-Physical Interaction** in this system is mediated by the **Control Application**, which generates and transmits control commands to the **Physical Crane** via the **Physical Crane Interface**. The **command types** include **optimal movement trajectories** (generated by the **Trajectory Generator Service**) with no residual swinging motion at the end. The **control message format** is not explicitly defined, but the system implies structured commands aligned with the crane’s kinematics model. **Validation and authentication mechanisms** are not explicitly described, though the **Continuous Validation Service** ensures executed trajectories match simulations, indirectly validating command execution. **Feedback systems** are present via the **Logging Application**, which captures real-time crane state data post-command execution. **Conflict resolution** is not detailed, but the **Dashboard** notifies operators if thresholds are breached, allowing manual intervention. **Command execution confirmation** is implied through the **Continuous Validation Service**, which compares executed trajectories against simulations and triggers alerts if discrepancies exceed thresholds."
]

instance dt_constellation : DTDFVocab:Constellation [
    base:desc "The Digital Twin constellation in the provided exemplars follows an **ad-hoc, lightweight orchestration pattern** without reliance on commercial frameworks. The **GreenhouseDT** exemplar uses **InfluxDB** (time-series database) and **ActiveMQ** (message broker) to manage **behavioral adaptation** between the physical greenhouse and its Digital Twin, with **virtual machines** hosting pre-recorded data for offline analysis. The **Air Quality Management** exemplar employs **AutomationML** for Digital Twin modeling and **Microsoft Azure tools** for pipeline implementation, indicating a **cloud-centric, service-oriented constellation** with **three distinct applications** (runtime visualization, simulation, prediction) coordinated via Azure’s ecosystem. The **gantry crane system** (logistics domain) adopts a **C4 Model architecture**, emphasizing **context and container diagrams** for software-hardware integration but lacks explicit details on system-wide coordination mechanisms. **Containerization/virtualization** (e.g., Docker, VMs) is a recurring theme for **modular deployment**, while **single-board computers (Raspberry Pi)** serve as edge nodes for sensor-data acquisition. No formal orchestration framework (e.g., Kubernetes, service mesh) is mentioned; coordination relies on **ad-hoc integration** of components."
]

instance fidelity_and_validity_considerations : DTDFVocab:FidelityConsideration [
    base:desc "The **GreenhouseDT** exemplar emphasizes **self-adaptive behavioral fidelity**, where both the physical greenhouse and its digital twin dynamically adjust to maintain synchronization. Validation is implied through **prerecorded data** in virtual machines, enabling offline testing of model accuracy against historical system behavior. The **Air Quality Management** exemplar focuses on **runtime validation** via three applications: **visualization** (real-time monitoring), **simulation** (scenario testing), and **prediction** (forecasting virus spread risks). Uncertainty quantification is not explicitly addressed, but the use of **Microsoft Azure tools** suggests cloud-based analytics for error detection (e.g., anomaly detection in sensor data). No formal **verification methods** (e.g., model checking, calibration protocols) or **quality assurance processes** are detailed, though the **ad-hoc architecture** implies iterative refinement based on empirical feedback. The **AutomationML** standard in the Air Quality exemplar may inherently support fidelity through structured model exchange, but no quantitative metrics (e.g., RMSE, confidence intervals) are provided."
]

instance dt_technical_connection : DTDFVocab:TechnicalConnection [
    base:desc "The **Digital Twin’s Technical Connection** relies on a **service-oriented architecture** with the following key elements: **Communication protocols** include **MQTT** for inter-service signaling (via the **MQTT Broker**) and unspecified protocols for data transmission between the **Physical Crane Interface** and **Logging Application**. The **network topology** is not explicitly detailed, but the system implies a **centralized architecture** with the **Database (TimescaleDB)** as the core data repository. **Bandwidth and latency requirements** are not quantified, but the **Continuous Validation Service** suggests low-latency communication to enable real-time trajectory comparison. **Reliability and redundancy mechanisms** are not described, though the **MQTT Broker** and **Database** imply fault-tolerant design. **Security protocols** are not mentioned, but the system’s reliance on **TimescaleDB** and **Grafana Dashboard** suggests standard database and web security measures (e.g., authentication, encryption) are assumed."
]

instance dt_hosting_deployment : DTDFVocab:Deployment [
    base:desc "The **Digital Twin’s Hosting and Deployment** infrastructure is not explicitly detailed in terms of cloud/edge/on-premise, but the system’s components suggest a **hybrid or on-premise deployment model**. The **Database (TimescaleDB)** and **MQTT Broker** imply **local hosting** for low-latency operations, while the **Dashboard (Grafana)** and **Simulation/Trajectory Services** may leverage **edge computing** for real-time processing. **Computational requirements** are not quantified, but the **Trajectory Generator Service** and **Simulation Service** require sufficient CPU/GPU resources for kinematics modeling and trajectory optimization. **Storage requirements** are met by **TimescaleDB**, which handles time-series data efficiently. **Scalability mechanisms** are not described, though the modular design (e.g., separate services) allows for potential horizontal scaling. **Availability/reliability assurance** is implied by the **Continuous Validation Service** and **Dashboard alerts**, but no explicit redundancy or failover strategies are mentioned."
]

instance horizontal_integration : DTDFVocab:HoriIntegration [
    base:desc "The Digital Twin systems exhibit **limited but domain-specific horizontal integration** with external systems. The **GreenhouseDT** exemplar integrates with **InfluxDB** (for time-series data storage) and **ActiveMQ** (for message brokering), but no external interoperability standards (e.g., OPC UA, MQTT) or enterprise system dependencies are documented. The **Air Quality Management** exemplar uses **AutomationML** for Digital Twin modeling and **Microsoft Azure tools** (e.g., Azure IoT, Logic Apps) for pipeline orchestration, implying **cloud-based integration** with potential enterprise systems via Azure’s native protocols (e.g., REST APIs, event grids). The **gantry crane system** (logistics domain) lacks explicit details on external integration but aligns with **cyber-physical system (CPS) architectures**, which typically rely on **industrial protocols** (e.g., OPC UA, PROFINET) for factory/warehouse integration. No cross-Digital Twin or enterprise system interoperability (e.g., federated twins, shared ontologies) is described; integration patterns are **domain-isolated** and **ad-hoc**, with no standardized protocols for data exchange between twins."
]

instance standardization : DTDFVocab:Standardization [
    base:desc "The **Air Quality Management** exemplar adheres to **AutomationML** for digital twin modeling, a standardized format for engineering data exchange, ensuring interoperability with other industrial systems. The **GreenhouseDT** exemplar does not explicitly mention compliance with industry standards but relies on **commonly used technologies** (InfluxDB, ActiveMQ) that are widely adopted in IoT and cyber-physical systems. Neither exemplar references **certification requirements** or **compliance frameworks** (e.g., ISO 22400 for digital twins, IEC 62443 for cybersecurity). The **lab-scale gantry crane** exemplar does not provide details on standardization, though its architecture is visualized using the **C4 Model**, a software-centric notation. **Interoperability standards** are only explicitly mentioned for AutomationML in the Air Quality Management case."
]